1. Misalignment Momentum ‚Äì ‚ÄúRelational Dissonance‚Äù

URFT Construct	Mathematical State	System Diagnostic	Operational Intervention (PantheonOS)
Misalignment Momentum	p = M(D_t F - \mathcal{R}(F)), with \|p\| \gg 0 or \|\Delta\| = \|D_tF - \mathcal{R}\| \gg 0	Relational Dissonance: The system‚Äôs actual motion is significantly deviating from its expected relational flow. Roles, identity, or behavior are ‚Äúoff-script‚Äù and tension is building.	Proof Forge + Hound: (1) Trigger a distortion minimization pass: adjust \dot F (behavior) OR refine \mathcal{R} (expectations/model) to reduce \|p\|. (2) Hound logs before/after \|p\| to validate improvement.


‚∏ª

2. Relational Curvature ‚Äì ‚ÄúContextual Instability‚Äù

URFT Construct	Mathematical State	System Diagnostic	Operational Intervention (PantheonOS)
Relational Curvature	F_A = \dot A + A^2; use scalar metrics like \text{Tr}(F_A^\top F_A) or \lambda_\text{max}(F_A). Large values: \|F_A\| \gg \text{baseline}.	Contextual Instability: Context is changing too fast or folding back on itself (self-referential/recursive paradox). Risk of thrash, burnout, or catastrophic reparameterization.	Mirror.guard + ChronosMesh: (1) Gauge Fixing: search for a G(t) that reduces \|F_A\|; if not possible, freeze A(t) (hold context constant). (2) ChronosMesh slows temporal modulation \gamma(t) to reduce new context injection.


‚∏ª

3. Relational Hamiltonian Drift ‚Äì ‚ÄúLoss of Coherent Ground‚Äù

URFT Construct	Mathematical State	System Diagnostic	Operational Intervention (PantheonOS)
Relational Hamiltonian	H(F,p,A,\Pi) with \frac{dH}{dt} \neq 0 in a regime where L is expected to be stationary (no major external shocks).	Loss of Identity / Coherent Ground: The system‚Äôs total relational ‚Äúaction potential‚Äù is drifting without a matching explanation (no explicit change in goals, metrics, or environment recorded).	ChronosMesh + Mother Duck: (1) Detect non-stationarity in inputs (R, L, environment). (2) If none found, log anomaly to Mother Duck and reduce step size / cadence via ChronosMesh. (3) Optionally trigger Oracle Weave to re-derive a consistent trajectory \gamma(t).


