5. Eigenmode Mismatch ‚Äì ‚ÄúRole / Purpose Ambiguity‚Äù

URFT Construct	Mathematical State	System Diagnostic	Operational Intervention (PantheonOS)
Eigenmode Mismatch	Ideal: \mathcal{R}(F^*) = \lambda F^*. Observed: \mathcal{R}(F) \neq \lambda F and \| \mathcal{R}(F) - \lambda_i F \| is large for all eigenpairs (\lambda_i, F_i).	Role / Purpose Ambiguity: Current state F is not close to any stable attractor of the relational dynamics. The system is ‚Äúbetween roles‚Äù or in a muddled configuration without clear vector.	Oracle Weave + Mirror: (1) Find nearest eigenmode F^* (or low-dimensional stable subspace). (2) Oracle Weave proposes convergence path: adjust \dot F toward \mathcal{R}(F^*). (3) Mirror reflects change and checks that the new role/purpose is consistent with constraints and invariants.


