6. Temporal Curvature ‚Äì ‚ÄúPhase of Flow‚Äù

URFT Construct	Mathematical State	System Diagnostic	Operational Intervention (PantheonOS)
Temporal Curvature Phase	Use \|F_A\| over time. Two regimes: (i) Flow: low, stable \|F_A\|\approx 0. (ii) Overdriven: sustained, high \|F_A\|.	Flow vs Overload: (i) When \|F_A\|\approx 0 and \|p\|\approx 0, system is in coherent, synchronized operation ‚Üí ‚Äúclean burn.‚Äù (ii) When \|F_A\| high but |p| still moderate, system is at risk of future misalignment.	Blink Protocol + Praus: (i) In low-curvature, low-misalignment: Blink Mode ‚Üí maximize throughput, permit higher relational complexity. (ii) In high curvature: invoke Praus (variance dampener) to reduce new inputs and narrow operational bandwidth until curvature drops.


